description:
Trx: Table containing Ericsson-specific attributes of radio transmission and reception (TRX) parameters for NR cells.

- dateTime: Timestamp indicating when the data was recorded.
- Area_Name: Name of the geographical area where the cell is located.
- CellId: Unique identifier of the cell.
- Id2: Redundant Cell ID, likely a copy of CellId.
- Id3:  Partial cell identifier, possibly indicating a sector or specific equipment.
- Id4:  Likely an index or flag related to the TRX within the cell.
- vsDataType: Type of data, specifying this as TRX data.
- vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format used.
- Trx.rfBranchRxRef: Reference to the receiver RF branch.
- Trx.userLabel: User-defined label (currently empty).
- Trx.combinedCellType:  Indicates if the cell is combined with other cells.
- Trx.reservedMaxTxPower: Maximum transmit power reserved.
- Trx.sectorEquipmentFunctionRef: Reference to sector equipment functions.
- Trx.noOfTxAntennas: Number of transmit antennas.
- Trx.rxImbMinNoOfSamples: Minimum number of samples for receiver imbalance measurement.
- Trx.arfcnMax: Maximum ARFCN (Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number).
- Trx.frequencyBand: Frequency band used by the TRX.
- Trx.configuredMaxTxPower: Configured maximum transmit power.
- Trx.trxId: TRX identifier within the cell.
- Trx.rxImbAlarmThreshold: Receiver imbalance alarm threshold.
- Trx.rfBranchRx: Reference to the receiver RF branch (potentially redundant).
- Trx.trxIndex: Index of the TRX.
- Trx.administrativeState: Administrative state of the TRX.
- Trx.rxImbSupWindowSize: Suppress window size for receiver imbalance.
- Trx.noOfRxAntennas: Number of receive antennas.
- Trx.arfcnMin: Minimum ARFCN (Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number).
